{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 12:12:37.684710", "event": "llm_end", "text": "**Network‑Level Diagnostic Report**\n\n| Item | Observation | Implication |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| **Host reachability** | `pc_0_0` (10.0.0.2) and `pc_0_1` (10.0.1.2) cannot exchange ICMP packets – ping results are *unknown* from the reachability test. | Indicates that the two hosts are not on a routable path. |\n| **Leaf router BGP advertisements** | `leaf_router_0_0` advertises `10.0.0.0/24`. <br> `leaf_router_0_1` advertises **only** `10.0.0.0/24` (no `10.0.1.0/24`). | The subnet that contains `pc_0_1` is never announced into the BGP fabric, so no route to `10.0.1.0/24` exists. |\n| **BGP neighbor state** | All eBGP peers are up, but the *State/PfxRcd* column shows `0` for the neighbor that should carry the missing prefix. | The neighbor is reachable but has no routes to advertise. |\n| **Routing tables** | `leaf_router_0_1` shows only the `10.0.0.0/24` route (via two paths). <br> `spine_router_0_0` and `spine_router_0_1` each have two paths to `10.0.0.0/24` but **no** entry for `10.0.1.0/24`. | The fabric has no knowledge of the second pod’s subnet. |\n| **Root cause** | Mis‑configuration on `leaf_router_0_1`: the network statement is wrong – it advertises the wrong /24 subnet. The correct configuration should advertise `10.0.1.0/24`. | Without the correct advertisement, hosts in that subnet cannot be reached from any other pod or from the super‑spine. |\n\n### Summary\n\nThe network is healthy in terms of link connectivity and BGP session establishment, but a single configuration error on `leaf_router_0_1` prevents the `10.0.1.0/24` subnet from being advertised. Consequently, `pc_0_1` is isolated from the rest of the Clos fabric, which explains the failed ping attempts. No other anomalies were detected.", "generation_info": {"model": "gpt-oss:20b", "created_at": "2025-12-12T12:12:36.655871577Z", "done": true, "done_reason": "stop", "total_duration": 9589288721, "load_dura